.m-o {

  position: fixed;

by removing the tick in this section, the screen can be scrolled downwards.

Not reproduced on my end. The website works fine as I said earlier.
Please write steps to reproduce in detail and also send the saved page to filters@adguard.com.

---

> .m-o { position: fixed; }

As I see, only `html` has this, so these rules may help.
```adblock
akakce.com#$#body { overflow: auto !important; }
akakce.com#$#html { position: unset !important; }
```

@zloyden This rule alone is enough to fix it.

akakce.com#$#html { position: unset !important; }

Thanks.
